by adding a NEW SECTION to read: Notwithstanding \u00a7 25-10-40, if the police officer or sheriff believes that the domestic violence perpetrator has a severe mental illness that makes the person an imminent danger to self or others, the officer or sheriff may initiate a mental illness hold under \u00a7 27A-10-3 and transport the person to an appropriate regional facility as described in that section and in accordance with the provisions set forth in title 27A. This section is not a substitution for an arrest under the provisions of chapter 25-10, and the person shall be released only to the custody of law enforcement or a law enforcement agency if the mental illness hold is released. 100 copies were printed on recycled paper by the South Dakota Legislative Research Council at a cost of $.161 per page. . Insertions into existing statutes are indicated by underscores. Deletions from existing statutes are indicated by overstrikes."}, {"bill_id": 7627, "bill_version_id": 43851, "bill_version": "House Judiciary Engrossed", "bill_version_date": "2017-02-03T13:13:37.663-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to allow law enforcement to initiate a mental illness hold in domestic violence situations. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That the code be amended by adding a NEW SECTION to read: Notwithstanding \u00a7 25-10-40, if the police officer or sheriff believes that the domestic abuse perpetrator has a severe mental illness that makes the person an imminent danger to self or others, the officer or sheriff may initiate a mental illness hold under \u00a7 27A-10-3 and transport the person to an appropriate regional facility as described in that section and in accordance with the provisions set forth in title 27A. This section is not a substitution for an arrest under the provisions of chapter 25-10, and the person shall be released only to the custody of law enforcement or a law enforcement agency if the mental illness hold is released. 100 copies were printed on recycled paper by the South Dakota Legislative Research Council at a cost of $.161 per page. . Insertions into existing statutes are indicated by underscores. Deletions from existing statutes are indicated by overstrikes."}, {"bill_id": 7627, "bill_version_id": 44150, "bill_version": "House Engrossed", "bill_version_date": "2017-02-08T16:27:50.97-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to allow law enforcement to initiate a mental illness hold in domestic abuse situations. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That the code be amended by adding a NEW SECTION to read: Notwithstanding \u00a7 25-10-40, if the police officer or sheriff believes that the domestic abuse perpetrator has a severe mental illness that makes the person an imminent danger to self or others, the officer or sheriff may initiate a mental illness hold under \u00a7 27A-10-3 and transport the person to an appropriate regional facility as described in that section and in accordance with the provisions set forth in title 27A. This section is not a substitution for an arrest under the provisions of chapter 25-10, and the person shall be released only to the custody of law enforcement or a law enforcement agency if the mental illness hold is released. 100 copies were printed on recycled paper by the South Dakota Legislative Research Council at a cost of $.161 per page. . Insertions into existing statutes are indicated by underscores. Deletions from existing statutes are indicated by overstrikes."}, {"bill_id": 7627, "bill_version_id": 45347, "bill_version": "Enrolled", "bill_version_date": "2017-03-02T11:26:08.227-06:00", "bill_text": ""}], "amendments": [], "fiscal_notes": [], "action_log": [{"bill_id": 7627, "action_date": "2017-01-25T14:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 43199, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/43199.pdf", "status_text": "First read in House and referred to", "journal_page": 